<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by DE:
[I]There are other ways to stay healthy besides potions. All of the meats and bread will raise your health although you have to wait after a couple of pieces because it will say your are full. Chicken raises your magic. You can kill bores, wolves, and rabbits everywere you go for food to keep you healthy. I cart aroudn as much meat as possible - and try to eat it first, instead of using potions. There are also cows, pigs and chickens to slaughter on the farms. The most useful skills for keeping yourself healthy are the Restore Health, I have only 1 skill point towards it and its plenty. I normally slug away and cast it. That way you only to keep yourselves stocked with magic potions. Other must have skills are two skills points to Alchemy. The first level is worthless because it only lets you mix some stuff, but with the second you can start making poitions with small empty bottles. Small empty bottles are cheap and often dropped. You just click on blue mushroom with your empty bottle and instant magic which is all you need if you have the restore health skill. The red mushrooms will give you health potions. I usually cart around about 20 small bottles of magic. Next you need weapons repair because as you weapon gets duller you start doing less damage and missing a lot more. Make sure you keep your weapons in good shape or your not going to get killing done.

